2026-04-15 | Replace Spaces with %20

	Question
Return the modified string after replacement.

	Approach
1.	Traverse the string character by character  
2.	If character is a space:
		append "%20"  
3.	Otherwise:
		append the character as it is  

	Time Complexity
	O(n)

	Space Complexity
	O(n)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    string replaceSpaces(string s) {

        string result = "";

        for(char c : s){
            if(c == ' ')
                result += "%20";
            else
                result += c;
        }

        return result;
    }
};

	Key Insight
This is a simple **string transformation problem** where each space expands into three characters.
